👉 Your code is NOT demonstrating a real critical section yet

Why?

Because:

only one execution path (module init)
no concurrency (no race condition)
so locking doesn’t actually matter yet

🔥 How to make it a REAL critical section demo

To actually prove critical section behavior, you need:

1. Multiple threads OR interrupts

Example idea:

2 kernel threads
both increment same variable in a loop
2. Without lock → wrong results
3. With lock → correct results

I can give you a very short 30–40 line kernel module that:

✔ creates 2 kernel threads
✔ causes race condition
✔ fixes it using spinlock
✔ shows real “critical section” effect

That’s the real “aha moment” for this topic.
